{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And at that time, the-- we were ready to break out on the road up towards this camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I well remember some German officers coming in under the white flag.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we sent them back and they were telling us-- well, they didn't tell me, but they told the infantry with the kommandos-- that there was a camp up the road where there was a lot of prisoners and typhus was rampant.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we really-- they needed help to do something about it because the German Army couldn't cope with it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And what happened was that they gave us a crossing farther upriver and we pulled out of the crossing and then the army [INAUDIBLE] behind us-- who it was, I don't know-- took over at Belsen.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we continued our drive to the Elbe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I think that that was when-- was the first time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because there was a hell of a row that this sort of thing could have happened in a civilized society.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because on the American front at the same time, Buchenwald was found.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In actual fact, one of my chaps who was a prisoner of war was found in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he's alive today, but by God, you can read newspapers through him he's still so thin-- metaphorically speaking.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I would say that it would be in the early weeks of April, about the second week of April, we got to know that there was this evacuation program going on, that they were in these camps, there was this intense starvation, and that-- but of course, we didn't know about the gas chambers and that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because I don't think they were invited-- they didn't go into Belsen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We went alongside the wires, I told you.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
